From 006187ad50f256dfb4f1018c01fd54bc2456fd66 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: jeeminso <jeeminso@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 14 Jun 2025 10:25:42 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Fix OOM caused by under-accounted memory usage in JSON result
 sets

The result set for HTTP requests is returned in JSON format, but
the memory accounting logic was type dependant. For example, a
double was counted as 8 bytes, even though in JSON it's actually
a string like "0.123456789" which should be counted as 11 bytes(
sizeof utf-8 * length). This led to under-accounting and
potential OOM.
